comment.text: This translation key is used for a button title displaying "Form Templates" and appears on a download dialog in the application.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "قوالب جاهزة" (qawālib jāhiza) is a possible translation, it's quite literal ('ready templates'). A more natural and idiomatic translation for 'Form templates' in a Saudi Arabian context might be something like 'نماذج جاهزة' (namādhij jāhiza) or 'تصاميم نماذج' (tasāmīm namādhij). The literal translation misses some of the nuance of the original term.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider 'نماذج جاهزة' (namādhij jāhiza) or 'تصاميم نماذج' (tasāmīm namādhij).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Modelli di moduli" is a literal translation, it's not the most natural or idiomatic Italian for "Form templates". It's a bit clunky and repetitive.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider "Modelli per moduli" or simply "Modelli di formulario" which is more commonly used in professional contexts.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Romanian translation "Șabloane formular" is not the most natural or accurate translation of "Form templates". While technically correct, it's a bit literal. A more common and natural translation would be "Modele de formulare" or "Șabloane de formulare".

The translation "ආකෘතිපත්‍ර අච්චු" is not the most accurate or natural rendering of "Form templates" in Sinhala. "අච්චු" (acchu) generally refers to molds or dies, which doesn't align with the concept of form templates.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using "ආකෘති පත්‍ර" (aakruthu patra) or "පත්‍ර ආකෘති" (pathra aakruthu). These options are more commonly used and accurately convey the meaning of form templates.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While "Mẫu biểu mẫu" is technically correct, it's a bit redundant. "Mẫu" already implies a form or template. A more natural and concise translation would be "Mẫu" or "Biểu mẫu".
